Thus (dearely beloved in the Lord) haue I briefly run over the expoſition of this firſt verſe, let me now vpon it build ſome doctrine, for the building vp of our ſelues in our holy faith. you will bee pleaſed to remember with mee, that Amos of a heardmen or a ſhepheard became a bleſſed Prophet to carry a terrible word, & fearefull meſſage from the living God, to the

 King, Nobles, Prieſts, and people of Iſrael. The doctrine to be grounded herevpon, I deliver in this propoſition;
God chooſeth vile and deſpiſed perſons, to confound the great and mightie.

Now by this Azzah, or Gaza, you are to vnderſtand the inhabitants of the city, & not them only, but alſo the borderers;
